The councillor representing Guringawa Ward of Kumbotso LGA of Kano State, Muslihu Yusuf Ali, has appointed 18 aides. In one of the appointment letters sighted by Daily Trust, the councillor said the appointees are to help him in discharging his responsibilities. “This is to notify the general public of the appointment of my aides. They are to assist me to discharge my responsibility in various endeavours to ensure development, progress, welfare, security and wellbeing of Guringawa community,” he said. The aides include;  Sulaiman Ibrahim Bako, Personal Assistant (PA), Yahaya Abdu Yahaya,  Principal Private Secretary (PPS), Kamalu Garba (Media)  and Usama Umar Zubair (Religious Affairs), among others . 